Ekurhuleni emergency services said they responded to the scene after reports of a blaze. JOHANNESBURG - Four people have been killed in a cooking oil tank explosion in a factory in Roodekop, Germiston, on Monday afternoon. Ekurhuleni emergency services said they responded to the scene after reports of a blaze. Officials said once the fire was extinguished, they discovered the charred bodies. EMS spokesperson William Ntladi said: “All of them so far are male and we’re still busy doing a search around the area to check whether there are only four dead people.”